<h2 id="simplesound" class="coloured">Simple Soundex search for a baptism</h2>

<p>Selecting <span class="btnPress">Revise Search</span> will allow you to do just that. (Whereas using the browser Back button will not keep all settings.)</p>
<p>Then you can add a tick to the <strong>Soundex</strong> box to use the Soundex algorithm on the name.</p>
<p>Please remember that Soundex always assumes that the first letter is correct. So you may need multiple searches with different first letters to check for say, Kendall and Rendall.</p>

